    "long_instructions": "### Make your third character's \"Walk Up\" song\r\n\r\nAlmost done. Time to code your third character's song. You know the drill. \r\n\r\n**Do This:**\r\n- Choose your third character. \r\n- Code a sequence of sounds under `when run`. \r\n- Make sure the beginning (Measures 1-2) build up to the middle (Measures 4-6) and that leads to the ending (Measures 7-8). *Note: Your song can be longer, but do not exceed 12 measures*. \r\n- When you have a sequence you like, drag the `3 triggered immediately` block to your workspace and move all the code under `when run` to the trigger block. \r\n- Press \"Run\" and then practice pressing \"1\", \"2\", or \"3\" to trigger each walk up song. ",
